{
  "rule": "weno5_advection",
  "metric": "Linf",
  "expected_min_order": 4.7,
  "notes": "Classical Jiang-Shu (1996) 5th-order WENO reconstruction on a uniform 1D Cartesian grid with periodic BC is theoretically O(dx^5) in L_inf for smooth solutions. The 4.7 floor accounts for the small accuracy hit from the nonlinear-weight recovery of linear weights (omega_k -> d_k) at finite eps = 1e-6 and leaves headroom for round-off."
}
